---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="RunnersHeart Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for the RunnersHeart app and its on-device health and workout data handling."
  lang="en"
>
  <article class="privacy-policy">
    <nav class="locale-switch" aria-label="Language selector">
      <a href="/runners-heart/privacy/" class="locale-pill is-active">EN</a>
      <a href="/runners-heart/privacy/ko/" class="locale-pill">한국어</a>
    </nav>

    <h1>RunnersHeart Privacy Policy</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>RunnersHeart is designed to help you train with heart rate zones while keeping your workout data on your own devices.</p>
      <p>This policy describes what the app accesses, how the information is used, and the choices you have.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Information We Access</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Heart rate data through Apple HealthKit</li>
        <li>Workout data such as time, distance, pace, and calories</li>
        <li>Route data for outdoor running workouts, when available</li>
        <li>Heart rate zone settings and related workout preferences</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To show live workout metrics during a run</li>
        <li>To calculate heart rate zones using supported methods such as %MaxHR or HRR</li>
        <li>To provide haptic feedback when your workout intensity changes</li>
        <li>To generate post-run analysis such as time in zone, route review, and training load</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Storage and Security</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Workout and health-related data stay on your device and within Apple HealthKit</li>
        <li>RunnersHeart does not operate a server for storing your workout history</li>
        <li>Synchronization between iPhone and Apple Watch uses Apple system frameworks</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We do not sell your personal data</li>
        <li>We do not upload your health or route data to third-party servers</li>
        <li>We do not share workout data with advertisers</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your Controls</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>You can manage HealthKit permissions in iOS settings at any time</li>
        <li>You can remove the app and manage Health data separately in the Health app</li>
        <li>You can review and export workout-related information through app features when available</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>For privacy questions, please contact <a href="mailto:oozoofrog@gmail.com">oozoofrog@gmail.com</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Effective Date</h2>
      <p>January 11, 2026</p>
    </section>

    <nav class="page-nav">
      <a href="/runners-heart/" class="nav-link">Home</a>
      <a href="/runners-heart/support/" class="nav-link">Support</a>
    </nav>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .privacy-policy {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 32px 24px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
    border-radius: 22px;
    box-shadow: 0 12px 36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    backdrop-filter: blur(22px) saturate(150%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(22px) saturate(150%);
  }

  .locale-switch {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .locale-pill {
    display: inline-flex;
    min-height: 36px;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0 14px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    color: #714855;
    border: 1px solid rgba(158, 49, 71, 0.08);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .locale-pill.is-active {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #9e3147, #bf4960);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .locale-pill:hover {
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    color: #9e3147;
  }

  .locale-pill.is-active:hover {
    color: #fff;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
    color: #3f1c27;
    margin-bottom: 30px;
    padding-bottom: 14px;
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--frog-green);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: #3f1c27;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  p,
  li {
    color: #5d4650;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  li + li {
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .page-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-top: 18px;
    border-top: 1px solid #eadfe2;
  }

  .nav-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 42px;
    padding: 0 18px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(112, 168, 80, 0.92), rgba(74, 142, 58, 0.92));
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .nav-link:hover {
    color: #fff;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .privacy-policy {
      padding: 24px 18px;
    }

    .locale-switch {
      justify-content: flex-start;
    }

    .page-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
